The paper deals with adversarial attacks on deep learning models, which is a common topic in the fields of machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG and cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a supervised denoising autoencoder network, which is a type of neural network commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the robustness of the method against blackbox and whitebox attacks, which are common in the field of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses a Langevin dynamics algorithm, which is a type of stochastic optimization commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
